
<purchabr>AMERICAN</purchabr> {<purchcode>AMR</purchcode>} SETS SCHEDULE FOR <acqabr>AIRCAL</acqabr> MERGER
    DALLAS, March 31 - <purchaser>AMR Corp's American Airlines</purchaser> unit said
it <status>plans to complete</status> the integration of <acquired>AirCal</acquired> into its
operations within four to five months.
    <purchabr>American</purchabr>'s merger with <acqabr>AirCal</acqabr>, announced last November,
received final approval from the Department of Transportation
yesterday.
    <purchabr>American</purchabr> said Richard D. Pearson, coordinator of the
airline's merger activities, will become chairman and chief
executive officer of AirCal during the period up to completion
of the merger.
    <purchabr>American</purchabr> said Pearson succeeds William Lyon, who has been
elected to AMR's board.
    It added that David A. Banmiller will continue as <acqabr>AirCal</acqabr>'s
president and chief operating officer.
